        <Parent_String>tubular drums with single head [300198349], tubular drums [300194009], struck drums [300041669], drums (membranophones) [300041729], membranophones [300041661], sound devices by acoustical characteristics [300041621], sound devices (equipment) [300387677], Sound Devices (hierarchy name) [300041619], Furnishings and Equipment (hierarchy name) [300264551], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Afro-Cuban drums having a long tapered or barrel-shaped shell up to about 90 cm deep and a single head about 25 to 30 cm in diameter, usually played with the hands; they are generally though not invariably played in pairs.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Tambores afrocubanos que tienen una concha larga y delgada o en forma de barril de hasta aproximadamente 90 cmts. de profundidad y una sola cabeza de alrededor de 25 a 30 cmts. de diámetro, que generalmente se tocan con las manos; por lo general aunque no siempre se tocan en pares.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Afrikaans-Cubaanse trommen met een lange, nauwtoelopende of tonvormige cilinder die wel 90 cm diep kan zijn, met één trommelvel van ongeveer 25 tot 30 cm in doorsnede, die meestal worden bespeeld met de handen; meestal maar niet altijd bespeeld in paren.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052488/Etnomusicologisch Centrum</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指古巴黑人所用的鼓，鼓身為長錐形一或桶狀，深度可達九十公分，單鼓面的直徑約二十五至三十公分，通常以手敲擊，雖並非一定，但康加鼓通常成雙演奏。
</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Afrokubanische Trommel mit einem langen, konischen oder fassförmigen Korpus, der bis zu 90 cm hoch ist, und einem einzigen Schlagfell von etwa 25 bis 30 cm im Durchmesser;  sie wird gewöhnlich mit den Händen und meist, jedoch nicht immer, paarweise gespielt.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
